data.prompt: In tropical Africa, under the scorching sun, a historic landscape emerges. Towering baobab trees and dense foliage line the humid air over still waters. Colonial remnants mingle with neglected villages in a region marked by shadows of the past. Stagnant waters hold lurking dangers, whilst the wind whispers tales of resistance against colonial rule. This is a view of modern-day Africa, in Southern Nigeria, featuring a dense tropical landscape rich in history and cultural significance. Bokeh. Low lighting. Shot from below.
